  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "General Worker & Delivery Driver",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p>Delivery Operations: Safely transport aquarium tanks, equipment, and livestock to various residential and commercial locations.</p><p>Installation Support: Assist the technical team in the physical setup of aquarium tanks, including positioning heavy tanks and arranging stands.</p><p>Maintenance Services: Perform routine maintenance tasks such as water changes, filter cleaning, and glass scrubbing to ensure healthy aquatic ecosystems.</p><p>General Logistics: Assist with loading/unloading goods and maintaining the cleanliness of the company vehicle.</p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>Valid Driving License: Must possess a clean driving record (Class 3 or equivalent).</p><p>Physical Fitness: Ability to lift and maneuver heavy aquarium equipment and tanks.</p><p>Team Player: A positive attitude and the ability to work well with others during installations.</p><p>Experience (Preferred): Prior experience in delivery or basic plumbing/aquarium hobbyist knowledge is a huge plus, but we are willing to train the right candidate.</p><p>Punctuality: Strong time-management skills to ensure deliveries and service appointments are met on schedule.</p>",
